Package org.kynosarges.tektosyne.graph

Interface GraphPath<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of all nodes in the Graph
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AStar

    public interface GraphPath<T>
    Represents the path of a GraphAgent across a Graph. Also provides the total path cost and the last node reachable with a given maximum cost.
    Version:
    6.0.0
    Author:
    Christoph Nahr

    • Method Detail

      • nodes

        List<T> nodes​()
        Gets all Graph nodes in the GraphPath. Never returns null, but may return an empty List.
        Returns:
        a List of all Graph nodes in the GraphPath

      • totalCost

        double totalCost​()
        Gets the total cost of the GraphPath. May return a non-positive value if nodes() is empty.
        Returns:
        the sum of the GraphAgent.getStepCost(T, T) results for all nodes()

      • getLastNode

        T getLastNode​(double maxCost)
        Gets the last GraphPath node reachable within the specified maximum cost.
        Parameters:
        maxCost - the maximum total path cost
        Returns:
        the last nodes() element whose total path cost does not exceed maxCost
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if maxCost is equal to or less than zero
        IllegalStateException - if the GraphPath contains invalid data
